note.text: L|SARS-CoV-2 Virus viral RNA is Not Detected.|RE^Remark^HL70364^^^^2.5.1|
L|This assay was completed using a Real Time-PCR (RT-PCR) or Transcription|RE^Remark^HL70364^^^^2.5.1|
L|Mediated Amplification (TMA) based COVID-19 assay.|RE^Remark^HL70364^^^^2.5.1|
L|The Aptima SARS-CoV-2 assay is a nucleic acid amplification test that is|RE^Remark^HL70364^^^^2.5.1|
L|equivalent to RT-PCR utilizing transcription mediated amplification (TMA)|RE^Remark^HL70364^^^^2.5.1|
L|technology for the qualitative detection of RNA from SARS-CoV-2 in clinical|RE^Remark^HL70364^^^^2.5.1|
L|specimens.|RE^Remark^HL70364^^^^2.5.1|
L|Not detected results do not preclude SARS-COV2 infection and should not be used|RE^Remark^HL70364^^^^2.5.1|
L|as the sole basis for patient management decisions. Negative results must be|RE^Remark^HL70364^^^^2.5.1|
L|combined with clinical observations, patient history, and epidemiological|RE^Remark^HL70364^^^^2.5.1|
L|information.|RE^Remark^HL70364^^^^2.5.1|
L|This test has been authorized by the FDA under an Emergency Use Authorization|RE^Remark^HL70364^^^^2.5.1|
L|(EUA). This test is only authorized for the duration of time the declaration|RE^Remark^HL70364^^^^2.5.1|
L|that circumstances exist justifying the authorization of an emergency use of in|RE^Remark^HL70364^^^^2.5.1|
L|vitro diagnostic tests for the detection of SARS-CoV-2 infection under section|RE^Remark^HL70364^^^^2.5.1|
L|564(b) (1) of the Act, 21 U.S.C. 360bb-3(b) (1), unless the authorization is|RE^Remark^HL70364^^^^2.5.1|
L|terminated or revoked sooner.|RE^Remark^HL70364^^^^2.5.1|
